description: A 'high status' Roman masonry building, dated based on coin evidence to the 2nd - 3rd CE. A religious interpretation has apparently been put forward, so possibly some kind of shrine or temple.
bibliography: Heawood, R, and B Robinson. “A Romano-British Site East of Hinxton Grange: A11 Stump Cross to Four Went Ways Road Improvement Scheme.” Oxford Archaeology East, 1998. https://doi.org/10.5284/1007464.
Martyn, Blick, Brindle, and et al. “East of Hinxton Grange (Cambridgeshire).” The Rural Settlement of Roman Britain: an online resource, 2015. https://doi.org/10.5284/1030449.
